# Prisma Models Overview

NeonDB Postgres with 15 Prisma models. Schema lives at `apps/web/prisma/schema.prisma`. Generated client output is `apps/web/lib/generated/prisma`.

## Model catalog

### Identity + preferences

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `User` | `id`, `suiAddress` (unique), `email` (unique, optional), `emailVerified` (mirrors Google OIDC `email_verified` claim — written on first sign-in via `/api/user/status`), `displayName`, `timezoneOffset`, `tosAcceptedAt` | Auth/login flow | `/api/user/status` upsert (PR-B2 retired the dedicated email-link routes) |
| `UserPreferences` | `contacts` (JSON address book), `limits` (JSON spend limits) | User | `/api/user/preferences`, `save_contact` tool |
| `LinkedWallet` | Up to 10 secondary Sui addresses for aggregated portfolio views | User | `/api/user/wallets` |

### Engine / conversation

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `ConversationLog` | Full chat transcripts (every role + content + toolCalls + tokensUsed + costUsd) | Engine | `/api/engine/chat` per turn |
| `SessionUsage` | Per-session token + cost rollup (drives billing gate) | Engine | `/api/engine/chat` end-of-session |
| `TurnMetrics` | Per-turn metrics (Spec 1) — latency, attemptId, modifiableFieldsTouched, pendingActionOutcome, writeToolDurationMs | Engine harness | `/api/engine/chat` (chat-time row), `/api/engine/resume` (updateMany on attemptId) |

### Silent intelligence (`<financial_context>` + context layers)

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `UserFinancialProfile` | Risk tolerance, goals, income bracket, horizon (Claude-inferred) | Cron | Daily Claude inference job |
| `UserMemory` | Up to 50 episodic facts (Jaccard dedup'd) | Cron | Per-conversation extraction |
| `UserFinancialContext` | Daily on-chain snapshot — savings/wallet/debt/HF/APY/recent activity | Cron | 02:00 UTC `financial-context-snapshot` job |
| `AdviceLog` | Recommendations the agent gave (last 30d rehydrated each turn) | Engine tool | `record_advice` tool |
| `PortfolioSnapshot` | Historical portfolio totals for timeline canvas | Cron | Daily snapshot job |

### Audric Pay + Audric Finance

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Payment` | Sent payments, payment links, invoices (status, amount, recipient) | Pay flows | `/api/payments/*` |

> **Removed in SPEC 17 (S.103, May 2026):** `SavingsGoal` model + 4 `savings_goal_*` engine tools + `/api/user/goals` routes + `GoalsPanel` UI + `openGoals` field on `UserFinancialContext`. The savings-goal layer wasn't producing observable agent behavior change. Track savings progress via `health_check` + `portfolio_overview` + `yield_summary`.

### Indexer / chain memory

| Model | What it stores | Owned by | Updated by |
|---|---|---|---|
| `WatchAddress` | Addresses the user has asked Audric to track | User | `/api/user/wallets` |
| `AppEvent` | App-side events the chain classifiers ingest (chip taps, sponsor failures, key flows) | App | Various event emitters |
| `ServicePurchase` | MPP service purchases via `pay_api` tool | Engine tool | `pay_api` execution |

## Where to write — only here, never in a route

Database writes are concentrated by domain to make audits + migrations sane:

| Domain | Write site |
|---|---|
| User identity | `apps/web/app/api/user/*` |
| Conversation | `apps/web/app/api/engine/chat/route.ts`, `apps/web/app/api/engine/resume/route.ts` |
| Telemetry | `apps/web/lib/engine/harness-metrics.ts` |
| Cron snapshots | `apps/web/app/api/internal/*` (called by t2000 cron with `x-internal-key`) |
| Pay flows | `apps/web/app/api/payments/*` |
| Engine tools that write Prisma | `apps/web/lib/engine/{advice-tool,goal-tools,contact-tools}.ts` |

If you find yourself reaching for `prisma.X.create` in a new place, ask whether the existing write site can absorb it. Drift in write sites → drift in invariants.

## Where to read — go through helpers when one exists

| Read | Helper | Don't write `prisma.X.findMany` for this |
|---|---|---|
| Portfolio | `getPortfolio(address)` | See `audric-canonical-portfolio.mdc` |
| Activity feed | `getActivity(...)` | `lib/activity-data.ts` |
| Last 30d advice | `buildAdviceContext(userId)` | `lib/engine/engine-context.ts` |
| Episodic memories | `buildMemoryContext(memories)` | `lib/engine/engine-context.ts` |
| Financial profile | `buildProfileContext(profile)` | engine + Prisma `UserFinancialProfile` |

Direct reads in route handlers are fine for one-offs. Pattern is: helpers when the read appears in 2+ places.

## Migrations

```bash
pnpm --filter audric-web prisma migrate dev --name <descriptive-name>
pnpm --filter audric-web prisma generate
```

After migration:
- Update this rule's catalog if a new model landed.
- If the model is read by the engine, update `engine-context-assembly.mdc` too.
- Add a `@@index` for any column you'll filter on. Postgres without indexes scales badly.

## What's banned

```typescript
// ❌ Direct prisma in a React component (server component or otherwise)
// — always go through an API route or server action.
import { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma';
export default async function Page() {
  const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id } });
}

// ❌ Cross-domain writes (e.g. engine tool writing User table)
// — engine tools write engine-owned models (AdviceLog) only.

// ❌ Silently dropping invariants
prisma.user.upsert({ where: { suiAddress }, ... });
// — always check email-linkage first (see zklogin-passport-flow.mdc).
```

## Cross-references

- Schema → `apps/web/prisma/schema.prisma`
- Generated client → `apps/web/lib/generated/prisma`
- Prisma singleton → `apps/web/lib/prisma.ts`
- Engine context that reads these → `engine-context-assembly.mdc`
- Cron jobs that write these → `cron-job-architecture.mdc`
